{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0197oennsBHKizQuxwaDa5tR","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have comprehensive information. Let me compile my findings into a complete report.\n\n## Summary of URL Routing for Runs Endpoints\n\nI've found all code related to URL routing for \"runs\" endpoints, including HTTP route definitions, gRPC service definitions, and query parameter handling. Here are my findings:\n\n### HTTP Web Routes (Web Handler)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\nThe web handler defines the following routes for runs:\n\n1. **HTML Routes:**\n   - `GET /{$}` → `handleProjectOverview` - Landing page with project overview\n   - `GET /runs` → `handleRunsList` - Lists all runs with optional project filter\n   - `GET /runs/{id}` → `handleRunDetail` - Individual run detail page\n\n2. **JSON API Routes:**\n   - `GET /api/runs` → `handleAPIRuns` - JSON API to list runs with optional project filter\n   - `GET /api/runs/{id}` → `handleAPIRunDetail` - JSON API for run details\n   - `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output` → `handleAPIStepOutput` - Step output logs\n   - `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` → `handleAPIStream` - Server-Sent Events stream for live logs\n   - `DELETE /api/runs/{id}/container` → `handleAPIDeleteContainer` - Remove retained container\n\n**Lines:** 139-158 in handler.go define route registration with `http.NewServeMux()`\n\n### Query Parameter Support for Project Filtering\n\n**Lines 248-249 and 447-448 in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`:**\n\n```go\nfunc (h *Handler) handleRunsList(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n    projectFilter := r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")\n    \n    var runs []*domain.Run\n    var err error\n    if projectFilter != \"\" {\n        runs, err = h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), projectFilter, time.Time{})\n    } else {\n        runs, err = h.store.ListRuns(r.Context(), time.Time{})\n    }\n```\n\nBoth `handleRunsList` (HTML) and `handleAPIRuns` (JSON) handlers:\n- Parse the `?project=` query parameter\n- Filter runs by project directory when provided\n- Return all runs when project filter is empty\n\n**Example URLs:**\n- `/runs` - all runs\n- `/runs?project=/home/user/myproject` - runs for a specific project\n- `/api/runs` - JSON: all runs\n- `/api/runs?project=/home/user/myproject` - JSON: runs filtered by project\n\n### Frontend JavaScript Implementation\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html`\n\n**Lines 53-66:** The frontend constructs URLs with project filter:\n\n```javascript\nfunction filterByProject(dir) {\n    if (dir) {\n        window.location.href = '/runs?project=' + encodeURIComponent(dir);\n    } else {\n        window.location.href = '/runs';\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Lines 62-66:** API polling also includes project filter in URLs:\n```javascript\nvar url = '/api/runs';\nif (currentProject) {\n    url += '?project=' + encodeURIComponent(currentProject);\n}\n```\n\n### gRPC Service Definitions\n\n**File:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n\n**Lines 12, 91-106:** gRPC service definition:\n```protobuf\nservice ClocheService {\n  rpc ListRuns(ListRunsRequest) returns (ListRunsResponse);\n}\n\nmessage ListRunsRequest {\n  bool all = 1;\n}\n\nmessage ListRunsResponse {\n  repeated RunSummary runs = 1;\n}\n\nmessage RunSummary {\n  string run_id = 1;\n  string workflow_name = 2;\n  string state = 3;\n  string started_at = 4;\n  string error_message = 5;\n  string container_id = 6;\n}\n```\n\n**Note:** The gRPC `ListRunsRequest` only has an `all` boolean flag (not project filtering). Project filtering is only available via HTTP web API.\n\n### gRPC Server Implementation\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n\n**Lines 377-399:** The gRPC `ListRuns` RPC method:\n- Takes a `ListRunsRequest` with an `all` flag\n- Filters runs from last hour unless `all=true`\n- Returns `ListRunsResponse` with `RunSummary` list\n- Does not support project filtering\n\n### Database Layer\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`\n\n**Lines 181-212:** `ListRuns` implementation:\n```go\nfunc (s *Store) ListRuns(ctx context.Context, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error) {\n    // SQL: SELECT ... FROM runs ORDER BY started_at DESC [WHERE started_at >= ?]\n}\n```\n\n**Lines 214-246:** `ListRunsByProject` implementation:\n```go\nfunc (s *Store) ListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error) {\n    // SQL: SELECT ... FROM runs WHERE project_dir = ? [AND started_at >= ?] ORDER BY started_at DESC\n}\n```\n\n### Store Interface\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`\n\n**Lines 15-16:** The `RunStore` interface defines:\n```go\nListRuns(ctx context.Context, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\nListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time) ([]*domain.Run, error)\n```\n\n### Test Coverage\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go`\n\n**Lines 270-335:** Comprehensive tests for project filtering:\n- `TestRunsList_ProjectFilter` - HTML endpoint with project filter\n- `TestRunsList_ProjectColumn` - Project column display\n- `TestAPIRuns_ProjectFilter` - JSON API with project filter\n\n**Test patterns show:**\n- Project filter passed via `?project=/home/user/alpha`\n- Both HTML and JSON endpoints support the same query parameter\n- Filtered results only contain runs matching the project directory\n\nAll key files are located in absolute paths in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/` for HTTP handling and `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/` for database queries."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a552ca3bceb57f9f4 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 64903\ntool_uses: 24\nduration_ms: 42251</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f1f0669a-686a-4b6d-807c-ce617681ff1b","uuid":"2b5dbafc-87d1-48fa-bf71-437169eea3a8","too