ate so it knows which option should be selected in the dropdown.\n\nFor the dropdown navigation logic, I'm writing a function that checks if a label is selected and either navigates to the project-specific runs page or back to the global runs view.\n\nThe API polling needs to match the URL structure—when viewing a specific project's runs, the JavaScript should poll the corresponding API endpoint for that project rather than the global runs endpoint.\n\nNow I'm mapping out the implementation across the handlers and templates: the handler needs new routes for project-specific runs pages and API endpoints, the runs template needs to switch from query parameters to label-based URLs with proper dropdown values, and the project pages need their links updated to point to the new URL scheme. I'll also need to clean up the old query parameter support and update the tests accordingly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":20476,"cache_read_input_tokens":34146,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":20476},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f1f0669a-686a-4b6d-807c-ce617681ff1b","uuid":"fcfd18c5-cd14-48b6-bdd9-7159e20d9791"}
